modules.description: Converts time zone values to and from JSON format using Yojson, supporting serialization and deserialization. Handles time zone data as strings, enabling parsing from standard identifiers like "America/New_York". Useful for persisting time zone settings in configuration files or APIs.

This module handles the conversion of time zone data to and from JSON using Yojson. It supports parsing and serializing time zones from standard identifiers like "America/New_York" to string representations. Key operations include converting time zones to JSON values and extracting time zones from JSON input. Example uses include saving time zone settings in configuration files or transmitting them over APIs.
